Only one would survive to live to adulthood, the last and youngest of the 20 little pigs.

Only one would survive to live to adulthood, the last and youngest of the 20 little pigs.

They would try to survive in a harsh world with the homes they would build, out of any materials that they could find. Many found that there homes could not withstand the forces of nature or the attacks of predators, and died soon after. Only one would survive to live to adulthood, the last and youngest of the 20 little pigs.

For you see, the 20th little pig built a house in a distant and hidden part of a forest, made up of bricks and mortar, and it was strong enough to withstand the forces of nature. However, unlike his siblings who had also built houses sturdy enough to stand against harsh winds and natural disasters, the 20th little pig had devised a way to avoid predators. He had built a massive underground bunker, with a maze of tunnels that he could use to escape from any predator should they try to break into his house. The bunker was well hidden, fortified, and stocked, able to sustain him if the predators were to break into his above home. He would often leave his house unlocked at night, while he slept underground in his bunker, to fool predators into thinking the home was already abandoned.
